@node main "Index of Additional Information"
@remark beginverbatim
 Our Solar System
 ================
 "The Digital Universe" provides detailed information on the Sun, the 9
planets, and all 61 known moons in our solar system.  As well, you can read
information about asteroids, comets, meteors, and the interplanetary medium
(the space between the planets).

        @{"The Sun                     " link object04100000}
        @{"Planets and their satellites" link ssobjects}
        @{"Asteroids                   " link chapters2.guide/asteroids}
        @{"Comets                      " link chapters2.guide/comets}
        @{"Meteors                     " link chapters2.guide/meteors}
        @{"Interplanetary medium       " link chapters2.guide/ipmedium}
        @{"Hypothetical objects        " link hypothetical.guide/main} (things which were once thought to exist)
        @{"Earth-orbiting satellites   " link satobjects}
        @{"Spacecraft                  " link spacecraft.guide/main}

 Elsewhere
 =========
 Detailed information is available for all of the @{"Messier" link define.guide/messier} objects, some @{"NGC" link define.guide/ngc} and
@{"IC" link define.guide/ic} objects, and several significant stars.

        @{"Deep Sky Objects            " link dsobjects} (Messier, NGC, IC objects)
        @{"Stars                       " link stobjects}
@remark endverbatim
@endnode

